can you add a bit more about what these properties are?
Can you link the D-Bus interface review for this?
Done
Done

But I don't think all the values pass.

Looking at 
        "ThrottleCause": {
            "enum": [
                "PowerLimit",
                "ThermalLimit",
                "ClockLimit",
                "Unknown",
                "OEM"
            ],
Done
Don't you need to map these from D-Bus to Redfish like https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/master/redfish-core/lib/systems.hpp#L620 (and a lot of other places?)
Done
Isn't this going to have to go to 1_18 for ManagementDetectedFault ?
Done

ManagementDetectedFault is not in the list of generated enums. OEM is missing in this list. 

https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/master/redfish-core/include/generated/enums/processor.hpp#L167
ManagementDetectedFault was added as part of the Processor v18.0 schema which should be releasing shortly.  https://www.dmtf.org/sites/default/files/standards/documents/DSP2046_2023.1WIP99.pdf
This commit will not be merged until the schema has been released.
I'm marking this WIP for now.  In the future, if you know there are still things to be done, please mark your commits WIP.

Okay. The only required change in the new schema was this one enum value and it was already approved.  I am just waiting for them to release 2023.1 which is supposed to be released very soon. There are no additional code changes expected here (unless there are additional review comments).

> There are no additional code changes expected here

The changes required here would be to move this over to the Redfish enum for this property (which would've immediately flagged that this wasn't in the schema).

To be more clear, once bmcweb has been updated the schemas for 2023.1, your enumeration will show up here: https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/00ef5dc6d410ab83302529f23919b3d91a35b5e3/redfish-core/include/generated/enums/processor.hpp#L83

>> The changes required here would be to move this over to the Redfish enum for this property

This function is translating the dbus value to the approved Redfish enum values (including the one new value from processor schema 1.18.0: ManagementDetectedFault). Are you saying this translation is not correct or needs to change?
Yes.  I linked you the enum that you should be using rather than hardcoding the strings.
Done
inline lambda should not be longer than 10 lines.
Most of the lambda functions in these files are all longer than 10 lines. I used existing code as examples.  I can split this into a wrapper call and new function, but seems overkill.
Done

Check if (ec.value() != EBADR) and return internal error like we do other places.
https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/master/redfish-core/lib/fabric_adapters.hpp#L77
If the interface is there but getAllProperties failed then don't we need to give internal error?
Done

rfCause.empty() will always evaluate to true because the dbusToRfThrottleCause function does not return an empty string.

dbusauseToRfThrottleCause is returning unknown if it is invalid type, shouldn't we return error for invalid type?

Should we ignore if it is unknown type? 
I am working on similar change in PCIeSlot, I am not sure which is right way.
https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/63041

Good point on empty call. Since Unknown is a valid Redfish throttle cause, I think it makes sense to return that value (instead of an error).  We know the processor is throttled at this point, but just not able to determine why.
I can remove empty check.
Also, considering you're using an enum that wasn't available on this Redfish version, you'll need to rev this.
This is the correct schema version that contains the enum ManagementDetectedFault (Processor 1.18.0) from https://www.dmtf.org/sites/default/files/standards/documents/DSP2046_2023.1WIP99.pdf
ACK.  It's interesting that this passes the service validator when 1.18 doesn't exist in the schema pack.  Oh well.

Please re-check your test results.  If processor 1.18 isn't present in the schema, this should've caused schema errors.  Can you please re-check that your tests passed before 2023.1 had been released?
Done
I've now rebased your patch on top of the WIP schema update.  Feel free to make your code changes, and this patchset will be rebased when the final 2023.1 is released.
2023.1 has been released, and the commit will merge shortly.  Please get this patch fixed up and it can merge as well.

Fixed the patchset to something that can merge.

@chris, can you please re-review and make sure that the changes I've made work for you.  Namely I:
1. Moved to using the generated enum, instead of hardcoded strings
2. Modified the flow such that "ThrottleReasons" is always produced if supported, even if the array is empty, which is generally what redfish would recommend, not changing the keys supported based on conditions.
Also, I made the code return internal error on GetAll error, and made both fields non-optional (I don't see any reason why a service would implement half of this interface).
Log BMCWEB_LOG_ERROR?
internalError logs to LOG_ERROR automatically.
Since Ed uploaded several patch sets, would be good if his name was here too, oh well.
can we remove this comment?
Done
